President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on May 6, 2020, honoring National Nurses Day. In the proclamation, he expressed gratitude and admiration for the extraordinary men and women who work as nurses, particularly during the coronavirus pandemic. He highlighted the selflessness, sacrifice, and dedication of nurses as they provide vital care and assistance to patients, often at their own risk. President Trump called upon the people of the United States to observe National Nurses Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.